<TITLE> NBR chases tax info on 53 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 5 (bdnews24.com)  The tax regulator has sought information on the bank accounts of 53 people including former FBCCI president Abdul Awal Mintoo, wife Nasrin Fatema Awal, Barisal city corporation mayor Mojibur Rahman Sarwar and his family members. Former prime minister Khaleda Zia's assignment officer Dr Firoz Mahmood Iqbal, former vice chancellor of Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujib Medical University Md Abdul Hadi, and former Awami League lawmakers Rafiqul Anwar and Noor-e-Alam Chowdhury Liton are also being investigated by the National Board of Revenue. Their wives and other family members are also part of the investigation. According to a letter signed by deputy director general of the NBR's central intelligence cell Shamima Akter: "It's necessary to examine the account information of these persons/taxpayers for proper internal auditing." bdnews24.com obtained a copy of the letter Thursday. The tax regulator has requested information from banks, going back to July 1, 2001, on savings accounts, term deposits, loan accounts, foreign currency accounts and credit cards held by those named individually or jointly. The NBR has asked banks to comply with their request by July 12. The NBR also moved to investigate nine companies: Superior Builders & Engineers, Superior Technologies, Superior Advertising Company, Titas Engineering Enterprise, AM Power Ltd, Mum Power Transformer, Mum Power Generations, Mum Power Cables and Debider Pharmaceuticals. Rokeya Sattar Foundation, controlled by Dr Firoz Iqbal's family, was also included in the NBR investigation. bdn
